1
00:01:03,159 --> 00:01:04,280
The weather bureau said "approximately"?

2
00:01:05,879 --> 00:01:07,200
"Approximately" isn't good enough.

3
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:08,680
I need exact wind direction and speed

4
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:10,400
at Black Eagle Beak within three hours.

5
00:01:11,439 --> 00:01:11,840
Right.

6
00:01:12,439 --> 00:01:13,040
One more thing.

7
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,519
Tell Doctor Li at the clinic

8
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:16,280
to bring hypothermia first-aid supplies

9
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:17,439
and report to the village committee now.

10
00:01:24,879 --> 00:01:25,319
Party Secretary.

11
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:26,400
We can't wait any longer.

12
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,120
Zhaxi and Jimei

13
00:01:28,599 --> 00:01:29,400
know the mountains well,

14
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,280
but Meiduo and Nana lack field experience.

15
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,319
Once hypothermia sets in,

16
00:01:32,319 --> 00:01:33,760
the golden rescue window is two hours.

17
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,079
I'll lead the team up.

18
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:38,280
Suolang and Ciren, come with me.

19
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:39,560
You wait at the pass as backup.

20
00:01:40,439 --> 00:01:41,040
Hold on, hold on.

21
00:01:41,359 --> 00:01:42,079
I'll go up the mountain.

22
00:01:42,319 --> 00:01:43,120
You wait at the pass.

23
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:44,799
Alright.

24
00:01:45,159 --> 00:01:45,719
Okay.

25
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,359
Careful.

26
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,079
Keep your weight back.

27
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:57,040
I think I see them.

28
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,120
Look.

29
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:00,400
Jimei!

30
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:01,319
Nana!

31
00:02:01,599 --> 00:02:02,400
Meiduo!

32
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:03,719
Zhaxi!

33
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:04,640
Meiduo!

34
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,680
Jimei!

35
00:02:06,079 --> 00:02:06,799
Are you guys okay?

36
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:07,920
We're fine.

37
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,000
How about you?

38
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,080
We're good.

39
00:02:10,639 --> 00:02:11,280
That's a relief.

40
00:02:12,639 --> 00:02:13,439
Let's head back, then.

41
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,039
The fog has cleared.

42
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,039
The rain's stopped too.

43
00:02:17,759 --> 00:02:18,879
Which way do we go?

44
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:22,240
Look over there.

45
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:24,840
See those seven stars?

46
00:02:25,479 --> 00:02:26,520
The handle points north.

47
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:28,719
Follow it, and we can make it down.

48
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:31,840
Will that really work?

49
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:33,759
Of course it will.

50
00:02:34,199 --> 00:02:35,120
My dad told me,

51
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:37,960
mountain folk never use maps at night,

52
00:02:38,159 --> 00:02:39,240
just the Big Dipper.

53
00:02:39,719 --> 00:02:41,319
It's always up there pointing the way.

54
00:02:41,719 --> 00:02:42,960
It's never wrong.

55
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,879
Scientifically speaking,

56
00:02:45,879 --> 00:02:47,800
the North Star sits near the North Pole,

57
00:02:48,159 --> 00:02:49,719
in a relatively fixed position.

58
00:02:49,879 --> 00:02:51,639
It really is the best reference point

59
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:52,599
for finding direction at night.

60
00:02:53,319 --> 00:02:53,840
See?

61
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,439
Even the scientist says so.

62
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:06,719
Zhaxi.

63
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,680
Party Secretary.

64
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,360
Zhaxi, can you hear me?

65
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:10,800
We've got a signal!

66
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,120
Are you all okay?

67
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,639
Everyone's safe and sound.

68
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:15,400
Getting ready to head down.

69
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:20,919
This color here

70
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:22,000
is called madder red.

71
00:03:22,319 --> 00:03:23,560
For this touch of red,

72
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,400
we nearly got stranded in the canyon.

73
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:27,080
I was so scared at the time.

74
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,199
I thought it was all over.

75
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:30,360
But Zhaxi

76
00:03:31,719 --> 00:03:33,919
pointed at the sky and said,

77
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:35,960
"Just follow the Big Dipper,

78
00:03:36,719 --> 00:03:37,639
and you won't get lost."

79
00:03:38,319 --> 00:03:39,080
So,

80
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:42,960
I got my most beautiful starry sky photo.

81
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:43,919
Pretty, right?

82
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,360
In the city, we have GPS now,

83
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,240
but I always feel anxious.

84
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,080
Always afraid of taking the wrong turn.

85
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:52,599
Now I get it.

86
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,520
As long as you dare to look up,

87
00:03:54,919 --> 00:03:56,000
the stars are always there.

88
00:03:56,479 --> 00:03:57,599
As long as you dare to slow down,

89
00:03:57,919 --> 00:04:00,360
and put your heart into it like Zhuoma,

90
00:04:00,719 --> 00:04:03,639
life will give you its truest colors.

91
00:04:10,439 --> 00:04:11,039
Meiduo.

92
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,240
What's up, Ajia Zhuoma?

93
00:04:12,479 --> 00:04:13,800
Why'd you call me out so urgently?

94
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:14,560
Come.

95
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:15,560
Look at this.

96
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,240
This one was grown in the greenhouse.

97
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:19,199
Looks tender, but wilts outside the lab.

98
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:20,480
Now take a look at this one.

99
00:04:22,639 --> 00:04:25,000
This color's a bit deeper.

100
00:04:25,639 --> 00:04:26,000
Right.

101
00:04:26,319 --> 00:04:27,600
It's all drawn out by UV rays.

102
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:28,879
To survive,

103
00:04:28,879 --> 00:04:31,199
it pumps out anthocyanin for protection.

104
00:04:31,399 --> 00:04:33,560
Like they say: the more it suffers,

105
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,600
the more beautiful the color.

106
00:04:35,079 --> 00:04:36,079
Don't give me all that.

107
00:04:36,079 --> 00:04:37,279
I'm busy inside.

108
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,560
Ajia Zhuoma,

109
00:04:39,439 --> 00:04:41,639
this is the Highland Red we need.

110
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:44,240
Dye extracted from this wild peach blossom

111
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,079
holds its color the best.

112
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,480
Our new Pulu color 2.0 is locked in!

113
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,480
Really?

114
00:05:36,639 --> 00:05:37,639
Thank you, Uncle Jimei.

115
00:05:37,639 --> 00:05:38,680
Thank you, thank you.

116
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,519
Uncle Jimei.

117
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,959
Is this the same peach blossom milk tea?

118
00:05:45,639 --> 00:05:46,199
Uncle Jimei.

119
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:47,480
This is a total hit!

120
00:05:48,439 --> 00:05:49,079
But...

121
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,040
I think we need a better name.

122
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:54,560
Isn't "peach blossom milk tea" too cheesy?

123
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,079
Yeah.

124
00:05:58,319 --> 00:05:59,959
It really is a bit tacky.

125
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,040
I think so too.

126
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,680
Me too.

127
00:06:03,319 --> 00:06:05,079
Then hurry up and think of another one.

128
00:06:09,839 --> 00:06:11,399
Xizang tea as the base,

129
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:12,959
Rhodiola for energy,

130
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:14,680
yak milk for richness,

131
00:06:14,839 --> 00:06:15,920
peach blossom for aroma.

132
00:06:16,639 --> 00:06:18,199
The proportions are just right.

133
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:23,920
Not too bitter, not too sweet.

134
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:25,920
Just right.

135
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,879
Just right.

136
00:06:31,319 --> 00:06:32,519
Then let's call it "Woqia."

137
00:06:33,199 --> 00:06:34,160
Woqia.

138
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,319
'Woqia' is Xizang language for milk tea.

139
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:41,319
"Qia" in Chinese means "just right."

140
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,839
Just like us,

141
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:45,800
brought here by fate, just right.

142
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:46,759
What do you all think?

143
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:47,959
Great, great, great!

144
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,000
See?

145
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:52,279
It honors the Xizang language heritage,

146
00:06:52,839 --> 00:06:54,120
and fits the online vibe too.

147
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:55,639
All right.

148
00:06:56,439 --> 00:06:56,959
Uncle Jimei.

149
00:06:57,279 --> 00:06:58,160
Strike while the iron's hot.

150
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:58,839
Make a few more cups.

151
00:06:59,199 --> 00:07:01,079
We'll film a promo for the festival.

152
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,079
Right?

153
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,600
Sure, no problem.

154
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:04,480
We'll...

155
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,720
just call it Woqia.

156
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,839
Woqia, Woqia, Woqia, Woqia!

157
00:07:06,839 --> 00:07:07,319
Cheers, cheers!

158
00:07:07,319 --> 00:07:08,319
Woqia!

159
00:07:10,759 --> 00:07:11,959
Dear friends,

160
00:07:12,399 --> 00:07:14,959
the 23rd Peach Blossom Culture Festival

161
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:17,360
is now officially open!

162
00:07:17,759 --> 00:07:19,240
Tashi Delek!

163
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:41,600
This year's Peach Blossom Fairy contest

164
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,600
is different from previous years.

165
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,560
All you visitors here today,

166
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:47,560
you're a vital part of it.

167
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,199
This time, the Peach Blossom Fairies

168
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:51,439
have to serve you at the scenic area

169
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:54,000
to earn your precious votes.

170
00:07:54,959 --> 00:07:56,480
Tashi Delek!

171
00:07:57,839 --> 00:07:58,720
Dear friends,

172
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,240
good afternoon, everyone.

173
00:08:05,639 --> 00:08:09,000
The Peach Blossom Fairy contest is open.

174
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:11,519
You've all just voted for

175
00:08:11,519 --> 00:08:12,240
the Peach Blossom Fairy

176
00:08:12,439 --> 00:08:13,680
in your hearts.

177
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,480
Next, we'll announce

178
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:18,639
this year's Peach Blossom Fairy winner:

179
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,920
Zhuoga!

180
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,759
Let's congratulate Zhuoga.

181
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,279
Please welcome Zhuoga with applause.

182
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,560
Thank you, everyone.

183
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:32,360
I grew up beside these peach groves.

184
00:08:32,519 --> 00:08:34,240
When the peach blossoms bloomed each year,

185
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:36,039
my mom would bring me here.

186
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:38,440
She said these were Nyingchi's best days.

187
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:41,360
I'm so happy to be standing here now.

188
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,360
I hope that every year from now on,

189
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:45,360
the peach blossoms will be this beautiful,

190
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,759
and everyone is doing so well.

191
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,559
Thank you. Thank you, Zhuoga.

192
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:51,759
Congratulations again to Zhuoga.

193
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:53,679
We also want to give a big thanks

194
00:08:53,679 --> 00:08:55,519
to our charity partners,

195
00:08:55,519 --> 00:08:56,840
Himalayan Sacred Tea

196
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,759
and China Jewelry.

197
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:01,919
It's the first time peach blossom pigment

198
00:09:01,919 --> 00:09:03,360
is used on Pulu fabric.

199
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:06,279
If it fades or doesn't catch on,

200
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,639
all my previous research will be wasted.

201
00:09:10,399 --> 00:09:11,600
Trust your skills.

202
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,440
This year is different.

203
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,200
We also have a special award,

204
00:09:15,679 --> 00:09:18,200
requested by our livestream viewers:

205
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,960
the Popularity Fairy award.

206
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,480
Let's give a round of applause

207
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:24,559
as the Popularity Fairy comes on stage.

208
00:09:42,919 --> 00:09:44,320
Has everyone noticed

209
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:47,639
that the outfit our Popularity Fairy wears

210
00:09:47,639 --> 00:09:49,159
is really special?

211
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:50,240
The fabric

212
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:52,080
uses our traditional

213
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:54,039
handwoven Pulu craftsmanship.

214
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:55,600
And the color

215
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:58,080
is extracted from the peach blossoms

216
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:00,639
that grow all around us.

217
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,919
It's a blend of modern and traditional.

218
00:10:04,159 --> 00:10:07,360
Let's congratulate Popularity Fairy Nana!

219
00:10:08,919 --> 00:10:09,960
Congrats, Nana!

220
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:10,799
And now,

221
00:10:10,799 --> 00:10:12,320
Nana, please share with us

222
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,639
your acceptance speech.

223
00:10:17,559 --> 00:10:20,000
Does everyone think the color of my dress

224
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:20,960
looks nice?

225
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,639
Beautiful!

226
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:24,240
The color of this dress

227
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:25,919
wasn't made with regular dye.

228
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,320
It was my dear friend,

229
00:10:27,679 --> 00:10:28,639
Dr. Meiduo,

230
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:31,159
who extracted it from the petals

231
00:10:31,159 --> 00:10:32,679
of our Nyingchi peach blossoms bit by bit.

232
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:33,960
So,

233
00:10:34,159 --> 00:10:36,840
she's the real Peach Blossom Fairy.
